    > Focus on serving others  rather then self 
        >> Philippians 2:3-4
            >>> "Do nothing from selfishness or empty conceit, but with humility of mind regard one another as more important than yourselves; do not [merely] look out for your own personal interests, but also for the interests of others."
Fear
    > an unpleasant often strong emotion caused by anticipation or awareness of danger 
    > Types of Fear 
        >> Situation-specific Fear
            >>> Fleeting Fear   
                >>>> When startled or surprised
            >>> Public Speaking
        >> Social Anxiety disorders
            >>> Fear of social interactions
        >> Panic Disorders  
            >>> individual experiences sudden, overwhelming fear or anxiety that may last several minutes. (Panic Attack)
        >> Post Tramatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
            >>> a recurring fear triggered by past trauma such as an accident, war, or another dangerous event.
        >> Phobia's
            >>> Arachniphobia
                >>>> Fear of Spiders
    > Signs of Fear
        >> Increased Heart rate
            >>> the increase in adrenaline produced to ready the body for the perceived threat causes the heart rate to increase
        >> Faster breathing or shortness of breath
        >> Butterflies or digestive changes
            >>> In response to fear or a threat the body produces cortisol which inhibits insulin production to ensure that the muscles have immediate energy (fight or flight). When threat is over this can cause the feelings of Butterflies in your stomach or nausea.
        >> Sweating or chills
            >>> Sweating is caused by the increase in adrenaline. Chills are because adrenaline stimulates muscle contraction which include the tiny muscles that surround hair follicles
        >> Trembling muscles
    > How to deal with Fear
        >> Short-lived fear can be good since it alerts you of a perceived threat that your body is aware of
        >> Can use breathing exercises to help manage your fear 
            >>> Deep breathing
            >>> Teddy bear breathing
            >>> 4-7-8 Breathing
            >>> Mindful Breathing
            >>> Diaphragmatic Breathing
            >>> Slow Breathing
            >>> Pursed-Lip breathing
            >>> Resonance Breathing
            >>> Yoga breathing
            >>> Alternate Nostril Breathing
        >> If breathing techniques don't work you can always turn to "talk therapy"
    > Scripture passages
        >> 2 Timothy 1:7
            >>> "For God has not given us a spirit of timidity, but of power and love and discipline."
        >> Isaiah 41:10
            >>> "'Do not fear, for I am with you; Do not anxiously look about you, for I am your God. I will strengthen you, surely I will help you, Surely I will uphold you with My righteous right hand.'"
        >> 1 John 4:18
            >>> "There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear involves punishment, and the one who fears is not perfected in love."
        >> Psalm 34:4
            >>> "I sought the LORD, and He answered me, And delivered me from all my fears."
        >> Joshua 1:9
            >>> "Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous! Do not tremble or be dismayed, for the LORD your God is with you wherever you go."
        >> Proverbs 29:25
            >>> "The fear of man brings a snare, But he who trusts in the LORD will be exalted."
        

    
